### Jakarta Bean Validation

Spring Boot supports Jakarta Bean Validation (previously Javax Validation) through annotations.

### Common Validation Annotations

| Annotation | Description |
|---|---|
| `@NotBlank` | String must not be null or whitespace |
| `@NotEmpty` | Collection/map must not be empty |
| `@NotNull` | Value must not be null |
| `@Size(min, max)` | String length or collection size |
| `@Min` / `@Max` | Numeric minimum/maximum |
| `@Email` | Valid email format |
| `@Pattern(regexp)` | Regex pattern match |
| `@Positive` / `@PositiveOrZero` | Positive numbers |
| `@Future` / `@Past` | Date in future/past |

### Request Body Validation

```java
public record CreateUserRequest(
    @NotBlank(message = "Name is required")
    @Size(min = 2, max = 100)
    String name,

    @NotBlank
    @Email
    String email,

    @Min(18) @Max(120)
    int age,

    @Pattern(regexp = "^\\+?[1-9]\\d{1,14}$")
    String phone
) {}

// In controller:
@PostMapping
public ResponseEntity<User> create(@RequestBody @Valid CreateUserRequest request) {
    // If validation fails, MethodArgumentNotValidException is thrown
}
```

### Custom Validators

```java
@Target(ElementType.FIELD)
@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)
@Constraint(validatedBy = UniqueEmailValidator.class)
public @interface UniqueEmail {
    String message() default "Email already exists";
    Class<?>[] groups() default {};
    Class<? extends Payload>[] payload() default {};
}

public class UniqueEmailValidator implements ConstraintValidator<UniqueEmail, String> {
    @Autowired private UserRepository userRepository;

    @Override
    public boolean isValid(String email, ConstraintValidatorContext context) {
        return email != null && !userRepository.existsByEmail(email);
    }
}
```

### Group Validation

```java
public interface CreateGroup {}
public interface UpdateGroup {}

@NotBlank(groups = CreateGroup.class)
private String id;  // Required on create, optional on update
```

